Wth October, 1698.—- The two bedchamberwomem above named, are buried alive, if we are to believe what rumor has bruited abroad. All the Boyars and magnates that were present at the Council by which the fate of the rebel Strelitz was decreed, this day were summoned to a new tribunal. A criminal was set before each, and each had to carry out with the ax the sentence which had passed.
